25|$|Chinese folk <b>religion</b> <b>is</b> <b>a</b> set {{of worship}} {{traditions of the}} ethnic deities of the Han people. It {{involves}} the worship of various figures in Chinese mythology, folk heroes such as Guan Yu and Qu Yuan, mythological creatures such as the Chinese dragon, or family, clan and national ancestors. These practices vary from region to region, and do not characterize an organized religion, though many traditional Chinese holidays such as the Duanwu (or Dragon Boat) Festival, Qingming, and the Mid-Autumn Festival come from {{the most popular of}} these traditions.|$|E
